CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1961, pg. A1 reads: "Staunch Protestor - Joseph Grenesha and representatives from several other Premier St. families, including two Negroes and several white persons, halted the immediate granting of a building permit to builder Joseph Kane.  Members of the Zoning Board of Adjustment, who previously had granted Kane a permit to build, held up any action until they can visit the area and appraise the lot and building plans. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Joseph Grenesha, wearing bow tie, holding cigarette in mouth, and George Barbour wearing eyeglasses, standing in permit office with other men and women
